t_sha":"5159b6d26288c121954a9cf0e388d5f72d58cb9a","position":"1784652890186301001-5e5575a1-1560-4bd2-8f59-597ad47f36cd"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"57af5ae70e3f31e99cb232944be3c8a7d06f8ff3ff5c4cefcaf2b8d4c2325745","event_uuid":"91ab648d-c75c-4128-849b-f4b20d1bf881","position":{"commit_sha":"433995507915c56475b6c3acf0083f8d0e3898bf","position":"1784653112455313406-91ab648d-c75c-4128-849b-f4b20d1bf881"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"323e8ae23fe25a48a8b0e9b95e4a36725da427f2db081d3cd7e40d23d7f0304d","event_uuid":"b0c3fe51-a3cd-4f7b-a68f-23f1e8e95e83","position":{"commit_sha":"d73de749068dea659f34bf97eacf77a648d21613","position":"1784653328248970001-b0c3fe51-a3cd-4f7b-a68f-23f1e8e95e83"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":null,"claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":null,"comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"SCOPE REFINEMENT (acceptance criterion): the completion verifier must be skipped for a duplicate/supersedes closure IF AND ONLY IF the ticket carries a VALID 'supersedes' or 'duplicates' link to another ticket. It is NOT a blanket exemption for the --class value alone: a --class duplicate/not_a_bug/escalated close with NO valid superseding/duplicating link MUST still run completion verification (else it becomes a trivial bypass). The exemption is gated on the existence of a valid link to another ticket, not on the class string.","timestamp":1784509342278172001},{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"REBAR-DEBUG DIAGNOSIS (2026-07-21)\n\nReproduction/localization: src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py validates only that a bug close_class is in txn.CLOSE_CLASSES, then always performs the file-impact precheck and llm.verify_completion(..., graph=False). It does not inspect the ticket's active deps/managed_refs for duplicates or supersedes. Those relations are valid non-blocking directional graph relations elsewhere, but no close-gate consumer exists.\n\nRoot cause: close classification and relationship evidence are recorded independently, while completion-gate applicability is based only on ticket type, gate enabled, force-close, and idea status. The legitimate non-completion state never reaches _completion_precheck.\n\nMinimal corrective seam: before billable verification, resolve active links and allow a narrowly matched exemption only when an eligible non-completion class is paired with the required valid live duplicate/supersedes target. Do not exempt on class alone. Record the basis in close audit state and add positive/negative lifecycle tests, including missing, dangling, wrong-direction, and mismatched-class links.\n\nNo code changed during this diagnostic run.","timestamp":1784653328248970001}],"created_at":1784509017922057001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"36734504-bccf-4ea5-8559-ce3ee8f3a43f","relation":"discovered_from","target_id":"e983-4df0-0d53-4811"},{"link_uuid":"35cab70f-5945-452a-af0f-61f334b8f9ea","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"992d-9d17-c6ac-4492"},{"link_uuid":"5d46ba6c-c3d5-4332-b127-0f4892dee56e","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"4636-432a-1871-4d74"}],"description":"The completion-verification close gate (_completion_precheck in src/rebar/_commands/transition_close.py) runs full LLM completion verification on EVERY non---force-close bug close, with NO awareness that some closes are legitimately NON-completion:\n\n- close_class handling (transition_close.py ~line 124): only validates that --class is a VALID bug-close value (bug_close_class_ok); it does NOT exempt the classes that mean 'there is no completion to verify' — duplicate, not_a_bug, escalated.\n- criteria scope (~line 172, graph=False): verifies only THIS ticket's OWN acceptance criteria; it does not consult the ticket's dependency graph for a supersedes/duplicates link. A bug that another ticket SUPERSEDES (its work has legitimately moved to the superseding ticket/epic) is still forced to prove its OWN completion, which by definition cannot pass.\n\nREPRO: bug e983-4df0-0d53-4811 is superseded by epic 992d-9d17-c6ac-4492 (a 'supersedes' link exists).  -> 'completion verification FAILED — 1 unmet criteria; not closing.' The only ways past are --force-close (a gate BYPASS) or the idea->closed exemption (a hack) — neither is a legitimate 'close as superseded'.\n\nEXPECTED: a close whose --class is duplicate/not_a_bug/escalated, OR whose ticket carries a supersedes/duplicates link to an open/valid ticket, should SKIP completion verification (there is no own-completion to verify) while still recording the class + link. Same class of gap as ed13/0e15 (a lifecycle requirement not propagated to a branch that should be exempt).\n\nDiscovered while superseding e983 into epic 992d during the rebar-debug batch.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","4636-432a-1871-4d74"],["relates_to","992d-9d17-c6ac-4492"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"5072e221-5f63-426f-9d77-ae9847f137e8","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":2,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["close-gate","completion-verifier","lifecycle"],"ticket_id":"eaa9-bdd9-55ed-47b4","ticket_type":"bug","title":"Completion-verification close gate ignores superseding/duplicate relationships and non-completion --class values","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["323d628d-8188-486d-b9cf-1279e63f561e","36734504-bccf-4ea5-8559-ce3ee8f3a43f","35cab70f-5945-452a-af0f-61f334b8f9ea","3a921ef6-bae3-46ec-90e6-80c93cb8514b","5d46ba6c-c3d5-4332-b127-0f4892dee56e","5072e221-5f63-426f-9d77-ae9847f137e8","5e5575a1-1560-4bd2-8f59-597ad47f36cd","91ab648d-c75c-4128-849b-f4b20d1bf881","b0c3fe51-a3cd-4f7b-a68f-23f1e8e95e83"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784653328248970002,"uuid":"0971bf61-ad55-449f-a97e-b1040410207f"}